The paper deals with the problem of calculating the frequencies of substrings in compressed text data, which is a problem in data mining and machine learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves the use of straight line programs (SLPs), which are a type of compressed representation of text data, suggesting that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for solving the problem, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
